coord_op_scope: Historical record only - superseded - see remarks.

coord_op_scope: For applications with an accuracy at 5 m level.

coord_op_scope: Residuals under 2 m.

coord_op_scope: Recommended transformation for UKCS and IrishCS petroleum purposes.

coord_op_scope: Historic record only - now superseded - see remarks.

coord_op_scope: Accuracy 1-2 metres.

coord_op_scope: Oil exploration. Accuracy better than 4m and generally better than 2m.

coord_op_scope: For oil exploration. Accuracy better than 4m and generally better than 2m.

coord_op_scope: Basin-wide mapping and analysis.
Public reference, land and photgrammetric survey, mapping.
remarks: Origin is station YAP SECOR AMS 1965.

coord_op_scope: Large and medium scale topographic mapping, cadastral and engineering survey.
information_source: US Geological Survey Professional Paper 1395; "Map Projections - A Working Manual"; J. Snyder.

coord_op_scope: Surveying, mapping and civil engineering purposes. Accuracy on main islands 9m, see remarks for accuracy on outlying islands. For an accuracy of a few tens of centimetres on all main and outlying islands use programme TKY2JGD.
remarks: Derived at Tokyo datum origin. Also used on remote islands with significantly less accuracy: Io-To 793m, Kitadaito and Minamidaito Jima 642m, Tarama and Minna Shima 560m, Ishigaki and Taketomi Jima 251m, Yonaguni Jima 248m.
information_source: Geographical Survey Institute, Japan: Manual of Coordinate Transformation to JGD2000 for Public Surveys. Also M Tobita, "Modern Geodetic Coordinate Systems and their Transformations", J. Geodetic Soc. Japan, Vol. 43, No.4, 231-235, 1997.

coord_op_scope: Surveying, mapping and civil engineering purposes. Accuracy on main islands 9m.
remarks: Parameter values from Tokyo to JGD2000 (1) (code 15483). Assumes JGD2000 and WGS 84 can be considered the same to within the accuracy of the transformation.

coord_op_scope: Accuracy generally better than 1m except in Amazon basin where it degenerates to 5m.
remarks: For transformation between SAD69 and WGS 84 see SAD69 to WGS 84 (14), tfm code 1877.
information_source: Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics (IBGE) resolution 01/05 of 25th February 2005.

coord_op_scope: Approximation using NTv2 method of results of FINELTRA programme to an accuracy of 0.01m except at boundary of the Geneva and Vaud cantons, in city of Geneva and in the main valleys of Valais canton where differences are up to 20 cm.
remarks: Derived from CHENyx06 dataset. For improved accuracy (0.01m) use CHENyx06 interpolation programme FINELTRA. Although the nodes of the CHENyx06 dataset are in the grid domain, CHENYX06.gsb is in the geographic CRS domain to enable usage of NTv2 method.

coord_op_name: TWD67 / TM2 zone 121 to TWD97 / TM2 zone 121 (1)
coord_op_scope: Accuracy 6.4m.
remarks: Derived at Hu Tzu Shan (23°59'N, 120°58'E). Residuals increase to maximum of 6.4m as distance increases from this point.
information_source: Aerial Survey Office, Taiwan Forest Bureau.

coord_op_scope: Derivation of gravity-related heights from GPS observations. Accuracy 0.2m within onshore area.
remarks: May be used for transformations from WGS 84 to IGN 1988 MG. Accuracy at each 0.025 deg x 0.025 degree grid node is given within the geoid model file.

coord_op_scope: Derivation of gravity-related heights from GPS observations. Accuracy 0.2m within onshore area.

coord_op_scope: Derivation of gravity-related heights from GPS observations. Accuracy 0.5m within onshore area.

coord_op_scope: Medium and small scale topographic mapping.
remarks: Projection parameters are identical to UTM zone 33N. Unlike UTM zone 33N, the SWREF99 TM is used throughout all Sweden.
information_source: Lantmateriverket (National Land Survey of Sweden). http://www.lantmateriet.se

coord_op_scope: Topographic mapping, engineering survey, cadastre.
remarks: At the municipal level alternative projections are found defined with different sets of False Northing and Easting, based on 100 km grid squares. This is denoted by the last part of the name.  For example 61:-1 means FN = -6100000 and FE = 100000 m.
information_source: Lantmateriverket (National Land Survey of Sweden). http://www.lantmateriet.se
